{"title_page": "Kleinarl", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name            = Kleinarl\n| native_name     = \n| settlement_type = \n<!-- Images     -->\n| image_skyline   = KleinarlWinter.jpg\n| imagesize       = \n| image_caption   = Kleinarl in winter\n| image_shield    = Wappen at kleinarl.png\n| shield_size     = 80x110px\n| shield_link     = \n<!-- Maps           -->\n| pushpin_map         = Austria\n| pushpin_mapsize     = 270\n| pushpin_map_caption = Location within Austria\n| image_map           = \n| mapsize             = \n| map_alt             =\n| map_caption         = Location within St. Johann im Pongau district\n<!-- Location    -->\n| coordinates       = {{coord|47|16|0|N|13|19|0|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type  = Country\n| subdivision_name  = [[Austria]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[States of Austria|State]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]]\n| subdivision_type2 = [[District (Austria)|District]]\n| subdivision_name2 = [[St. Johann im Pongau District|St. Johann im Pongau]]\n| parts_type        = \n| parts_style       = para\n| p1                = \n<!-- Leaders -->\n| leader_title  = [[Burgomaster|Mayor]]\n| leader_name   = Max Aichhorn\n| leader_party  = {{Polparty|Austria| [[\u00d6sterreichische Volkspartei|\u00d6VP]] }}\n| leader_title1 = \n| leader_name1  = \n<!-- Statistics -->\n| area_footnotes   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_footnotes}}\n| area_total_km2   = {{Austria population Wikidata|area_total_km2}}\n| area_metro_km2   = \n| elevation_m      = 1014\n| elevation_max_m  = \n| elevation_min_m  = \n| population_as_of = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Austria population Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_urban =  \n| population_metro =  \n| population_note  = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| established_title = \n| established_date  = \n| timezone          = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| timezone_DST      = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset        = +1\n| utc_offset_DST    = +2\n| registration_plate = [[Vehicle registration plates of Austria|JO]]\n| postal_code_type   = [[List of postal codes in Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 5603\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 06418\n| website   = [http://www.kleinarl.at/ www.kleinarl.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n'''Kleinarl''' is a municipality in the [[St. Johann im Pongau (district)|St. Johann im Pongau district]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[Salzburg (state)|Salzburg]].\n\n==Geography==\n[[File:Kirche-Kleinarl1.jpg|thumb|left|Parish church]]\nThe municipal area is located in the Pongau region within the [[Central Eastern Alps]], on the northern rim of the [[High Tauern]] national park. The [[Radstadt Tauern]] mountain range with the source of the [[Enns (river)|Enns]] river separates it from the Salzburg [[Tamsweg District|Lungau]] region. In the south, it borders on the market town of [[Wagrain]].\n\nThe ''Flachauwinkl\u2013Kleinarl'' ski area is part of the [[Ski Amad\u00e9]] network. The inhabitants mainly depend on winter tourism, but hiking and cycling in summer is also popular.\n\n==History==\nThe [[Gothic architecture|Gothic]] St. Lawrence parish church was consecrated in 1443. It was rebuilt from 1984 to 1986 according to plans by [[Heinz Tesar]]. The [[Archbishopric of Salzburg|Prince-Archbishops of Salzburg]] had a hunting lodge erected at Kleinarl, which since the mid 18th century serves as a vicarage.\n \n===Population===\n{{Historical populations\n|align=left\n|1971|593\n|1981|651\n|1991|724\n|2001|743\n|2010|783 \n}}\n{{clear-left}}\n\n==Notable people==\n*[[Annemarie Moser-Pr\u00f6ll]] (born 1953), skier\n*[[Cornelia Pr\u00f6ll]] (born 1961), skier.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Kleinarl}}\n*[http://www.kleinarl.at/system/web/default.aspx Municipal site] {{