{"title_page": "Klagenfurt Cathedral", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox religious building\n| building_name         =Klagenfurt Cathedral\n| infobox_width         =\n| image                 =Klagenfurt Domplatz Kirche 22022007 01.jpg\n| image_size            =\n| alt                   =\n| caption               =The cathedral with the Domplatz in the foreground\n| map_type              =Austria\n| map_size              =\n| map_caption           =\n| location              =[[Klagenfurt]], Austria\n| geo                   = {{coord|46.623991|14.312207|display=inline,title}}\n| religious_affiliation = [[Catholic Church]]\n| rite                  = [[Latin Rite|Latin]]\n| region                =\n| state                 =\n| province              =\n| territory             =\n| prefecture            =\n| sector                =\n| district              =\n| cercle                =\n| municipality          =\n| consecration_year     =\n| status                =[[Cathedral]]\n| functional_status     =\n| heritage_designation  = \n| leadership            =\n| website               =\n| architect             =\n| architecture_type     =\n| architecture_style    =[[Baroque]]\n| founded_by            =\n| funded_by             =\n| general_contractor    =\n| facade_direction      =\n| groundbreaking        =\n| year_completed        =\n| construction_cost     =\n| capacity              =\n| length                =\n| width                 =\n| width_nave            =\n| height_max            =\n| dome_quantity         =\n| dome_height_outer     =\n| dome_height_inner     =\n| dome_dia_outer        =\n| dome_dia_inner        =\n| minaret_quantity      =\n| minaret_height        =\n| spire_quantity        =\n| spire_height          =\n| materials             =\n| nrhp                  =\n| added                 =\n| refnum                =\n| designated            =\n}}\n{{expand German|Klagenfurter Dom|date=March 2019}}\n'''Klagenfurt Cathedral''' ({{lang-de|Klagenfurter Dom; Dom- und Stadtpfarrkirche Hll. Petrus und Paulus}}) is the [[cathedral]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gurk|Roman Catholic Diocese of Gurk-Klagenfurt]] and also the main parish church of [[Klagenfurt]]. It was built by [[Protestantism|Protestants]] and dedicated to the [[Holy Trinity]] in 1581, and was the largest Protestant church in [[Austria]] at that time. It was commissioned by Christoph Windisch, Klagenfurt' s first mayor.<ref name=Klagenfurt>{{cite web|title=Klagenfurt Cathedral|url=http://conf.ifit.uni-klu.ac.at/erweb2005/klagenfurt_links.html|accessdate=28 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224815/http://conf.ifit.uni-klu.ac.at/erweb2005/klagenfurt_links.html|archive-date=3 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>  In 1600, during the [[Counter-Reformation]], it was given to the [[Society of Jesus|Jesuits]] and rededicated to Saints [[Saint Peter|Peter]] and [[Saint Paul|Paul]]. The church was razed to the ground by a fire and had to be rebuilt in 1724. Bishop Franz Xaver von Salm-Reifferscheidt made it the cathedral of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gurk|Diocese of Gurk]] in 1787.\n\n<gallery heights=220 mode=packed>\nFile:Klagenfurt Dom.JPG|Front view of the Klagenfurt Cathedral\nFile:Austria Klagenfurt Dome 01.jpg|Interior of the cathedral\nFile:Austria Klagenfurt Dome 08.jpg|The cathedral's altar\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Austria]]\n[[Category:Klagenfurt]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Carinthia (state)]]\n[[Category:Baroque architecture in Austria]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox religious building\n| building_name         =Klagenfurt Cathedral\n| infobox_width         =\n| image                 =Klagenfurt Domplatz Kirche 22022007 01.jpg\n| image_size            =\n| alt                   =\n| caption               =The cathedral with the Domplatz in the foreground\n| map_type              =Austria\n| map_size              =\n| map_caption           =\n| location              =[[Klagenfurt]], Austria\n| geo                   = {{coord|46.623991|14.312207|display=inline,title}}\n| religious_affiliation = [[Catholic Church]]\n| rite                  = [[Latin Rite|Latin]]\n| region                =\n| state                 =\n| province              =\n| territory             =\n| prefecture            =\n| sector                =\n| district              =\n| cercle                =\n| municipality          =\n| consecration_year     =\n| status                =[[Cathedral]]\n| functional_status     =\n| heritage_designation  = \n| leadership            =\n| website               =\n| architect             =\n| architecture_type     =\n| architecture_style    =[[Baroque]]\n| founded_by            =\n| funded_by             =\n| general_contractor    =\n| facade_direction      =\n| groundbreaking        =\n| year_completed        =\n| construction_cost     =\n| capacity              =\n| length                =\n| width                 =\n| width_nave            =\n| height_max            =\n| dome_quantity         =\n| dome_height_outer     =\n| dome_height_inner     =\n| dome_dia_outer        =\n| dome_dia_inner        =\n| minaret_quantity      =\n| minaret_height        =\n| spire_quantity        =\n| spire_height          =\n| materials             =\n| nrhp                  =\n| added                 =\n| refnum                =\n| designated            =\n}}\n{{expand German|Klagenfurter Dom|date=March 2019}}\n'''Klagenfurt Cathedral''' ({{lang-de|Klagenfurter Dom; Dom- und Stadtpfarrkirche Hll. Petrus und Paulus}}) is the [[cathedral]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gurk|Roman Catholic Diocese of Gurk-Klagenfurt]] and also the main parish church of [[Klagenfurt]]. It was built by [[Protestantism|Protestants]] and dedicated to the [[Holy Trinity]] in 1581, and was the largest Protestant church in [[Austria]] at that time. It was commissioned by Christoph Windisch, Klagenfurt' s first mayor.<ref name=Klagenfurt>{{cite web|title=Klagenfurt Cathedral|url=http://conf.ifit.uni-klu.ac.at/erweb2005/klagenfurt_links.html|accessdate=28 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303224815/http://conf.ifit.uni-klu.ac.at/erweb2005/klagenfurt_links.html|archive-date=3 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>  In 1600, during the [[Counter-Reformation]], it was given to the [[Society of Jesus|Jesuits]] and rededicated to Saints [[Saint Peter|Peter]] and [[Saint Paul|Paul]]. The church was razed to the ground by a fire and had to be rebuilt in 1724. Bishop Franz Xaver von Salm-Reifferscheidt made it the cathedral of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Gurk|Diocese of Gurk]] in 1787.\n\n<gallery heights=220 mode=packed>\nFile:Klagenfurt Dom.JPG|Front view of the Klagenfurt Cathedral\nFile:Austria Klagenfurt Dome 01.jpg|Interior of the cathedral\nFile:Austria Klagenfurt Dome 08.jpg|The cathedral's altar\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic cathedrals in Austria]]\n[[Category:Klagenfurt]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Carinthia (state)]]\n[[Category:Baroque architecture in Austria]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Klagenfurt_Cathedral"}
